value.name: San Pedro, Los Angeles - Wikipedia
value.snippet: San Pedro (/ s æ n ˈ p iː d r oʊ / san PEE-droh; Spanish: "St. Peter") is a neighborhood within the City of Los Angeles, California. Formerly a separate city, it consolidated with Los Angeles in 1909. The Port of Los Angeles, a major international seaport, is partially located within San Pedro.

value.name: Home | San Pedro Downtown Waterfront
value.snippet: San Pedro is located just 20 miles south of downtown Los Angeles and is home to North America's largest port at the LA Waterfront. This growing seaside town has nationally recognized landmarks, a thriving arts scene, and ocean-based adventures. There's no place like San Pedro. value.name: San Pedro de Alcantara, Costa del Sol – tourist guide, facts and map
value.snippet: San Pedro enjoys a long golden, sandy beach, backed by a palm lined promenade and some great chiringuitos (beach restaurants). Eating out San Pedro has an excellent choice of bars and restaurants. For traditional and lively Spanish dining, head to Alfredo Restaurants in the old town.

value.name: Biografia de San Pedro
value.snippet: San Pedro (detalle de un retrato de Rubens, c. 1611) San Pedro carecía de estudios, pero pronto se distinguió entre los discípulos por su fuerte personalidad y su cercanía al maestro, erigiéndose frecuentemente en portavoz del grupo. A través de los evangelios puede trazarse un perfil bastante completo de su personalidad.

value.name: San Pedro Guide: Experience, Benefits, & Side Effects - Third Wave
value.snippet: San Pedro ( Trichocereus / Echinopsis pachanoi) is a thin, columnar cactus native to the Andes mountains in South America (Argentina, Bolivia, Colombia, Chile, Ecuador and Peru) that contains mescaline —one of the longest-studied psychedelics in the world—and the first to be labeled with the term “psychedelic.”.
